attributes.narrative: Patient presents with an itchy rash on the arm that started three days ago. The rash is splotchy, circular, larger than a quarter, expanding, with redder edges and a non-red center. The patient describes it as very itchy and concerning. The patient is experiencing anxiety and panic, particularly worried about a potential worm infection. The patient has a history of panic disorder and has run out of medication.
